Parallel Sort wrapper using kit::psort()

Source: R/helpers.R
strsort.Rd

Parallel Sort wrapper using kit::psort()

Usage

strsort(x)

Arguments

x

<character> vector. If other, will default to base::sort()

Value

x in sorted order

Examples

strsort(random_hcpcs())
#>  [1] "00"    "0637T" "26568" "29"    "31"    "32555" "352"   "37"    "591"  
#> [10] "6319"  "7013"  "7215"  "8253"  "84"    "90"    "91111" "9501"  "9657" 
#> [19] "A62"   "A621"  "C"     "C1719" "C8927" "C92"   "E0"    "E25"   "G21"  
#> [28] "G4010" "G976"  "J"     "J108"  "J268"  "J3070" "J3121" "L3"    "M1"   
#> [37] "M10"   "M1038" "Q4"    "Q42"   "S55"   "T"     "T10"
